{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SnowLayerGeometry",
        "description": "Single-layer snow-pack geometry for the CLMU urban canopy thermal stack: given the total snow depth z_sno, computes the bottom-layer thickness, node depth, and top interface depth used by the snow conduction column. Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:33 (`SnowLayerGeometry` @component). Implements Oleson et al. (2010, CLM Tech Note Ch. 4) §4.1 Eqs. 4.9-4.10 in the simplest snl = -1 (single snow layer) regime, where Δz_0 = z_sno (pp. 92-93). Parameterized as observed-only: z_sno is the input (parameter); Δz_snow_0, z_node_snow_0, z_interface_snow_neg1 are the algebraic outputs of three identity/linear equations.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "snow",
            "temperatures",
            "geometry",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-12T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-in7e)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., G. B. Bonan, J. J. Feddema, M. Vertenstein, and E. Kluzek (2010). Technical Description of an Urban Parameterization for the Community Land Model (CLMU). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-480+STR. Chapter 4, Section 4.1 (Snow layer geometry), Eqs. 4.9-4.10, pp. 92-93."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SnowLayerGeometry": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:33\nUpstream `SnowLayerGeometry` is an MTK `@component` with one `@parameters` input (z_sno), three time-indexed `@variables` outputs (Δz_snow_0, z_node_snow_0, z_interface_snow_neg1), and one `@constants` declaration (zero_m = 0.0 m). Three algebraic equations close the system: Δz_snow_0 ~ z_sno, z_node_snow_0 ~ zero_m - 0.5*Δz_snow_0, z_interface_snow_neg1 ~ zero_m - Δz_snow_0.\n\nThe upstream `@constants begin zero_m = 0.0, [unit = u\"m\"] end` is encoded here as a zero-default parameter (units m). This mirrors the convention used by sibling observed-only ESM files in this rig that translate `@constants` to fixed-default parameters so the units flow through MTK's unit checker: snow_soil_blended_heat_capacity.esm encodes C_ice the same way, and snow_melt_no_layers.esm uses zero_kgm2 / zero_m for the same reason.\n\nThe component represents the snl = -1 single-snow-layer case from Oleson pp. 92-93: when z_sno spans the single-layer regime (0.01 ≤ z_sno ≤ 0.03), all snow lives in layer 0, so Δz_0 = z_sno, node z_0 sits at the layer midpoint, and the top interface z_{h,-1} sits at the surface offset by Δz_0. Multi-layer snow (snl < -1, requiring procedural branching on snow depth) is not exposed here — the upstream component's docstring notes that multi-layer packing logic is procedural and typically handled outside the equation system.\n\nUnicode `Δz_snow_0` is preserved from upstream — the schema's identifier pattern allows it and other temps/ ESM components already use unicode delta in identifiers (snow_melt_no_layers.esm uses `Δt`, snow_soil_blended_heat_capacity.esm uses `Δz`).\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — each output variable is given by a single algebraic equation in terms of parameters and the other outputs (no derivatives, no time-dependent dynamics). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by sibling observed-only ESM files (snow_soil_blended_heat_capacity.esm, snow_melt_no_layers.esm, total_phase_change_energy.esm).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1.0e-10): three algebraic identity/linear equations (no ODE integration). Δz_snow_0 ~ z_sno is exact assignment; z_node_snow_0 and z_interface_snow_neg1 involve one subtraction (and one halving) of the parameter, so roundoff is at the IEEE-754 ULP level (~1e-16). The upstream test uses `rtol = 1.0e-10` (test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:33-36) and we mirror that for fidelity. Tighter `abs: 1e-12` is asserted on outputs that take their full magnitude from z_sno in the zero-input regime so the assertion does not silently accept a stuck-at-zero regression."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-10
            },
            "variables": {
                "z_sno": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Total snow depth (Oleson Ch. 4 §4.1 — single-layer regime input, 0.01 ≤ z_sno ≤ 0.03 m for snl = -1)"
                },
                "zero_m": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero depth reference for the snow column (upstream @constants zero_m = 0.0 m; encoded as a fixed-default parameter so the units flow through MTK's unit checker)"
                },
                "Δz_snow_0": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Thickness of bottom snow layer (layer 0); Eq. 4.9 single-layer case: Δz_0 = z_sno"
                },
                "z_node_snow_0": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Node depth of bottom snow layer (Oleson Eq. 4.9): z_0 = z_{h,0} - 0.5·Δz_0 with z_{h,0} = 0 (surface), so z_0 = -0.5·Δz_0 (negative = above ground)"
                },
                "z_interface_snow_neg1": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Interface depth above bottom snow layer (Oleson Eq. 4.10): z_{h,-1} = z_{h,0} - Δz_0 with z_{h,0} = 0, so z_{h,-1} = -Δz_0 (negative = above ground)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "Δz_snow_0",
                    "rhs": "z_sno"
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "z_node_snow_0",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            "zero_m",
                            { "op": "*", "args": [0.5, "Δz_snow_0"] }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "z_interface_snow_neg1",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": ["zero_m", "Δz_snow_0"]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_equation_verification",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `SnowLayerGeometry - Equation Verification` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:23-40) at the single-layer canonical depth z_sno = 0.02 m (inside the 0.01-0.03 m single-layer band, pp. 92-93). Expected: Δz_snow_0 = 0.02 m (identity), z_node_snow_0 = -0.01 m (midpoint), z_interface_snow_neg1 = -0.02 m (top interface at -Δz_0). Anchors fidelity to the upstream Julia component at the same parameter value with rtol = 1.0e-10.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_sno": 0.02
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_snow_0",            "time": 0.0, "expected":  0.02 },
                        { "variable": "z_node_snow_0",        "time": 0.0, "expected": -0.01 },
                        { "variable": "z_interface_snow_neg1","time": 0.0, "expected": -0.02 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "zero_snow_depth",
                    "description": "Sign-agnostic zero-depth limit: at z_sno = 0 all three outputs collapse to zero (Δz_0 = 0, z_0 = 0, z_{h,-1} = 0). Confirms the equations propagate exact zero and the linear/identity equations are not silently biased; an abs tolerance is asserted so a stuck-at-zero regression cannot pass.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_sno": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_snow_0",            "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "z_node_snow_0",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "z_interface_snow_neg1","time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "thin_snow_lower_bound",
                    "description": "Lower end of the single-layer band: z_sno = 0.01 m (the threshold for snl = -1 per Oleson pp. 92-93). Δz_snow_0 = 0.01, z_node_snow_0 = -0.005, z_interface_snow_neg1 = -0.01. Sweeps the small-value side of the linear identity to confirm node placement at the layer midpoint.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_sno": 0.01
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_snow_0",            "time": 0.0, "expected":  0.01 },
                        { "variable": "z_node_snow_0",        "time": 0.0, "expected": -0.005 },
                        { "variable": "z_interface_snow_neg1","time": 0.0, "expected": -0.01 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "thick_snow_upper_bound",
                    "description": "Upper end of the single-layer band: z_sno = 0.03 m (the threshold for transition to snl < -1 per Oleson pp. 92-93). Δz_snow_0 = 0.03, z_node_snow_0 = -0.015, z_interface_snow_neg1 = -0.03. Exercises the high end of the band; outside this regime the upstream model would assign more layers (procedural, not modeled here).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_sno": 0.03
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_snow_0",            "time": 0.0, "expected":  0.03 },
                        { "variable": "z_node_snow_0",        "time": 0.0, "expected": -0.015 },
                        { "variable": "z_interface_snow_neg1","time": 0.0, "expected": -0.03 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "node_at_layer_midpoint",
                    "description": "Invariant: the node z_0 always sits at the midpoint of layer 0, halfway between the surface (z = 0) and the top interface z_{h,-1}. Equivalently, z_node_snow_0 = 0.5 · z_interface_snow_neg1. Asserted at z_sno = 0.025 m via both outputs to lock the relationship between Eqs. 4.9 and 4.10.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "z_sno": 0.025
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Δz_snow_0",            "time": 0.0, "expected":  0.025 },
                        { "variable": "z_node_snow_0",        "time": 0.0, "expected": -0.0125 },
                        { "variable": "z_interface_snow_neg1","time": 0.0, "expected": -0.025 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "single_layer_geometry_sweep",
                    "description": "Sweep snow depth z_sno across the single-layer band (0.01-0.03 m per Oleson pp. 92-93) at 11 evenly spaced points. Surfaces the three linear/identity outputs as functions of z_sno: Δz_snow_0 traces the 1:1 identity line, z_node_snow_0 traces a slope -1/2 line through the origin, and z_interface_snow_neg1 traces a slope -1 line. The three lines fan out from the origin and confirm the layer-midpoint placement geometrically.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "z_sno",
                                "range": { "start": 0.01, "stop": 0.03, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "layer_thickness",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Δz_snow_0 vs z_sno: 1:1 identity line over the single-layer band per Eq. 4.9 (single-layer case).",
                            "x": { "variable": "z_sno",     "label": "z_sno (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "Δz_snow_0", "label": "Δz_snow_0 (m)" }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "node_depth",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "z_node_snow_0 vs z_sno: slope -1/2 line per Eq. 4.9 (layer-midpoint node placement).",
                            "x": { "variable": "z_sno",         "label": "z_sno (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "z_node_snow_0", "label": "z_node_snow_0 (m)" }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "top_interface_depth",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "z_interface_snow_neg1 vs z_sno: slope -1 line per Eq. 4.10 (top interface at z_{h,0} - Δz_0 with z_{h,0} = 0).",
                            "x": { "variable": "z_sno",                "label": "z_sno (m)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "z_interface_snow_neg1","label": "z_interface_snow_neg1 (m)" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
